cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.GT, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents an algorithmic study of the Directed Feedback Vertex Set problem, which is a classic problem in algorithmic graph theory. This makes cs.DS a likely category for this paper. 
2. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper deals with the problem of finding a feedback vertex set in a directed graph, which is a problem in discrete mathematics. 
3. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper mentions the case when the input digraph is planar, which suggests a possible connection to computational geometry. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The problem of finding a feedback vertex set has applications in game theory, which makes cs.GT a possible category for this paper. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper mentions the Exponential Time Hypothesis, which is a central concept in computational complexity theory. This makes cs.CC a possible category for this paper.
